{"lemma":"تِرْكَةُ","slug":"تِرْكَةُ","root":"ت.ر.ك","root_slug":"ت-ر-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ر-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3904","n3910","n3911","n3912"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3904","headword_ar":"تَرَكَهُ","root":"trk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokN","text_ar":"تَرْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trokaAnN","text_ar":"ترْكَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (Fr, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left it, forsook it, relinquished it, abandoned it, deserted it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quitted it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intentionally, and by choice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by constraint, and of necessity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left it, forsook it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., as above; namely, a thing that he desired, or wished for, and also a thing that he did not desire, or did not wish for: (Ibn-'Arafeh, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left it, quitted it, went away from it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed from it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a place: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left him, forsook him, relinquished him, abandoned him, deserted him, quitted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separated himself from him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cast it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threw it, away, as a thing of no account; rejected it; discarded it; cast it off; left it off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left it, left it alone, let it alone; ceased, desisted, forbore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstained, from it; neglected it, omitted it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left it undone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~aAhu","text_ar":"خَلَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, O;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadaEahu","text_ar":"وَدَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"At~rkhu","text_ar":"اتّركهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K. [But respecting this latter verb, see what follows.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@toruki","text_ar":"وَا@تْرُكِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaHora rahowFA","text_ar":"البَحْرَ رَهْوًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xliv. 23,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And leave thou the sea opened with a wide interval;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same state as before thy passing through it, and strike it not with thy rod, nor alter anything thereof; (Bd;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless, parted asunder;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel;) so that the Egyptians may enter it; (Bd, Jel;) is an instance of the verb meaning leaving intentionally, and by choice: (Er-Rághib, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo tarakuwA mino jan~aAtK waEuyuwnK","text_ar":"كَمْ تَرَكُوا مِنْ جَنَّاتٍ وَعُيُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the next verse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How many gardens and springs did they leave!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel,) is an instance of the verb meaning leaving by constraint, and of necessity. (Er-Rághib, TA.) In a phrase such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka Haq~ahu","text_ar":"تَرَكَ حَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"claim, to be null,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rejected it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka rakoEapN mina AlS~alaApi","text_ar":"تَرَكَ رَكْعَةٌ مِنَ الصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He neglected, omitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left unperformed, a"},{"kind":"page_break","n":305},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rkEp","text_ar":"ركعة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the prayer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it is said (but I think it doubtful) that] the verb, having an ideal substantive for its objective complement, is used metaphorically. (Msb.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla fiyhi famaA A@t~araka","text_ar":"قَالَ فِيهِ فَمَا ا@تَّرَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"تَرَكَ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strove, laboured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerted himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aijotahada","text_ar":"اِجْتَهَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in it, and neglected not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"omitted not, anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"in his power]: the verb is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^awoSaY biAlv~uluvi walamo","text_ar":"مَنْ اَوْصَى بِالثُّلُثِ وَلَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoy^FA","text_ar":"شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yat~ariko","text_ar":"يَتَّرِكْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wlm yatoruko $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"ولم يَتْرُكْ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wlm","text_ar":"ولم"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yat~ariko","text_ar":"يَتَّرِكْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoy^FA","text_ar":"شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famaA A@t~araka","text_ar":"فَمَا ا@تَّرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for this verb is not trans., except, sometimes, in poetry; and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walamo yatoruko fiymaAA^u*ina lahu fiyhi $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"وَلَمْ يَتْرُكْ فِيمَااُذِنَ لَهُ فِيهِ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who bequeaths the third"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his property,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and does not omit anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"of what he is allowed (to leave, or anything of the third part, for this is all that he is allowed to bequeath)]: it is from the saying ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala famaA A@t~araka","text_ar":"فَعَلَ فَمَا ا@تَّرَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and neglected not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"omitted not, anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka Almay~itu maAlFA","text_ar":"تَرَكَ المَيِّتُ مَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The deceased left property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watarakonaA Ealayohi fiY AlA=xiriyna","text_ar":"وَتَرَكْنَا عَلَيْهِ فِى الا=خِرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) in the Kur [xxxvii. 76 &c.], (TA,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have perpetuated"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, Jel, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"a eulogy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the later generations"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel, TA) of the prophets and peoples to the day of resurrection, [namely,] Salutation &c. (Jel.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aroku","text_ar":"التَّرْكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaEolu","text_ar":"الجَعْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, K, TA,) in some instances; (Lth, TA;) as though it had two contr. significations: (K:) [i. e.,] when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka","text_ar":"تَرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is doubly trans., it has the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~ara","text_ar":"صَيَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala","text_ar":"جَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakotu AlHabola $adiydFA","text_ar":"تَرَكْتُ الحَبْلَ شَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered, the rope strong;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused it, to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) So too in the Kur ii. 16,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watarakahumo fiY ZulumaAtK","text_ar":"وَتَرَكَهُمْ فِى ظُلُمَاتٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And maketh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causeth, them to be in darknesses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd, MF.) And sometimes one says of any action that has come at last to a certain state,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tarakotuhu ka*aA","text_ar":"مَا تَرَكْتُهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not make it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cause it, to be thus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarika","text_ar":"تَرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokN","text_ar":"تَرْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, IAar)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"married,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took to wife, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tariykap","text_ar":"تَرِيكَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman that had remained a virgin, unmarried, until she had become of middle age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long after she had attained to puberty, in the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent, of her parents."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Fr","K","Msb","MF","TA","Jel","Lth","IAar","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n3910","headword_ar":"تَرْكَةٌ","root":"trk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tariykapN","text_ar":"تَرِيكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboEapN","text_ar":"رَبْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of middling stature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ibn-'Abbád, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokaAtN","text_ar":"تَرْكَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a Alxaliylu A_ilaY mak~apa yuTaAliEu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ الخَلِيلُ اـِلَى مَكَّةَ يُطَالِعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokatahu","text_ar":"تَرْكَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Khaleel"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. Abraham)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to Mekkeh to get knowledge of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trkp","text_ar":"تركة"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning Hagar, and her son Ishmael: (K:) the word originally means an ostrich's egg, and is here used metaphorically; for the ostrich lays but one egg in the year, and then leaves it and goes away: (TA:) Z says, in the Fáïk, that it is thus related, with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent; (Nh, O, TA;) but it would be a proper way if it were with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarikatahu","text_ar":"تَرِكَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing that he had left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsaken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Nh, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3911","headword_ar":"تِرْكَةٌ","root":"trk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3912","headword_ar":"تَرِكَةٌ","root":"trk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is left, forsaken, relinquished, abandoned, deserted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quitted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalibapN","text_ar":"طَلِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ a thing desired, or sought; ” (TA;) see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokapN","text_ar":"تَرْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": particularly, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inheritance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property that is left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a person deceased; (S, Msb, K; *) also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tirokapN","text_ar":"تِرْكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarikaAtN","text_ar":"تَرِكَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}